<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="110" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1230,1472]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,534,1266,1292]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Report associated with sponges:</emphasis>
This species was reported among 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bowerbank, 1862 Marine Schmidt" authorityYear="1870" box="[922,1061,1267,1292]" class="Hexactinellida" family="Farreidae" genus="Farrea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sceptrulophora" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="occa">
<emphasis box="[922,1061,1267,1292]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Farrea occa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(&quot;Kinuami-kaimen” in Japanese) collected from the depths of Sagami Bay, 
<collectingCountry box="[674,738,1303,1329]" name="Japan" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Japan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kishida, K." box="[753,910,1302,1328]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" pagination="978" refId="ref17109" refString="Kishida, K. (1927) Ushio-dani, Ushio-dani-ka [Halacarus spongiphilus, Halacaridae]. In: Nippon Doubutsu Zukan [Illustrated Encyclopedia of Japanese Animals]. Hokuryukan, Tokyo, pp. 978. [in Japanese]" type="book chapter" year="1927">Kishida 1927</bibRefCitation>
). This was also again reported on a dictyonine sponge at 
<quantity box="[311,410,1338,1365]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="9.7" metricValueMin="9.3" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" unit="m" value="95.0" valueMax="97.0" valueMin="93.0">93–97 m</quantity>
depth in Sagami Bay (
<bibRefCitation author="Abe, H." box="[666,782,1338,1364]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" pagination="109 - 117" refId="ref12420" refString="Abe, H. (2010) Redescription of the First Japanese Halacarid Mite, Halacarus spongiphilus (Arachnida: Acari: Halacaridae). Species Diversity, 15, 109 - 117. https: // doi. org / 10.12782 / specdiv. 15.109" type="journal article" year="2010">Abé 2010</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1230,1472]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,269,1374,1400]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Remarks:</emphasis>
This species was redescribed on the basis of newly collected specimens by 
<bibRefCitation author="Abe, H." box="[1130,1262,1374,1400]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" pagination="109 - 117" refId="ref12420" refString="Abe, H. (2010) Redescription of the First Japanese Halacarid Mite, Halacarus spongiphilus (Arachnida: Acari: Halacaridae). Species Diversity, 15, 109 - 117. https: // doi. org / 10.12782 / specdiv. 15.109" type="journal article" year="2010">Abé (2010)</bibRefCitation>
. “It is not clear whether this mite is a parasite on its sponge host, or just a commensal making use of the sponge for habitation” (
<bibRefCitation author="Abe, H." box="[205,322,1446,1472]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" pagination="109 - 117" refId="ref12420" refString="Abe, H. (2010) Redescription of the First Japanese Halacarid Mite, Halacarus spongiphilus (Arachnida: Acari: Halacaridae). Species Diversity, 15, 109 - 117. https: // doi. org / 10.12782 / specdiv. 15.109" type="journal article" year="2010">Abé 2010</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
